content.description:
Climb the easy highly featured face (somewhat friable rock) behind the pine tree.  A bolt protects easy moves getting onto a small ledge.  Climb past 2 bolts on small holds (crux) to easier terrain.  A final bolt protects the last set of moves before the difficulties cease.  The last bolt protects two options for the final section, left up the seam, or right up the face.  The seam may be slightly harder.

Although the hard moves on this route are well protected the easier climbing is not.  Probably not a sport route even though the crux climbs like one.

The climbing is decent, if it was a little more continuous it would rate more stars.
content.location:
Left of

Cool Hand Luke

, on the largest clean face.  Starts immediately behind the large obvious pine tree on the highly featured face.

content.description: Crux is from bolts 1-3. Follow to bolt line and join the last bolt of Cool Hand Luke.
content.location: Between Cool Hand Luke and No Width

content.description: 2 or 3 stars - your choice.  Crux is moving above ramp.
content.location: Climb starts left of White Lies, goes up patina face to left trending ramp and up to arete then up and trending right to White Lies anchors

content.description: Follow the varied crack to its end
content.protection: Gear to 3", move left to the shared anchors

content.description: Follow the decent hand crack system up and left, pushing past two bushes.
content.protection: Gear to 2", shared anchors with Cool Hand Luke
content.location: Located on the left side of the mouth of Garbage Gully, this crack system is on the right side of the patina wall with two bushes guarding the crack.

content.description: Mule Skinner is the steep arete located half-way up Garbage Gully on the left.  Belay from down low below the route on a small loose platform.  Start by stick-clipping the 1st  and 2nd bolts.  As of 6/2017 there is a long stick at the base.
content.location: Garbage Gully is located 100 m down Pine Creek Canyon from Scheelite Gully.  From flame thrower etc, cross the canyon (following a trail) over to the other side of the canyon and past the short steep routes nearby Bavarian Tower.  Exit Scheelite and go slightly down canyon before heading straight back up-hill into Garbage Gully.

climbs.name: Eddie Van Halen
climbs.fa: Lance Milo Cagle, Austin Archer, Herman Harrison

content.description: A super stellar moderate. 150' of mostly crack climbing. Follow flakes and cracks, up and right, around the giant alcove in the middle of the Garbage Gully wall. The first crux is a beautiful 10b roof move that exits a beauty dihedral. The higher crux is 10c, well protected, and strangely awkward and "balancy".
content.protection: 10 bolts, and a single rack. A few extra hand size pieces, and lots of long runners, are recommended.   2 rappels.
content.location: RNTF is on the front face of Garbage gully, as opposed to the 'gully'. Just right of White Lies, and Just to the right of "The Tree".

climbs.name: Cool Hand Luke
climbs.fa: Zeke Federman, Nick Farley, Luke Tierstreip

content.description: Trend up and right on nice edges
content.protection: 7 bolts with bolted anchors on top.  To reduce rope drag, skip the 5th bolt.
content.location: Located on the left side of the mouth of the gully is a nice orange patina face with a few bushes on the right side of the wall.  Cool Hands Luke starts at an udercling on the far left-hand side of this wall.
